
---


@startuml
skinparam linetype ortho

' Actors
actor "Visitor" as Visitor
actor "User" as User
actor "Administrator" as Admin

' Classes
class WebPortal {
    +version: String
    +url: String
    +catalog: Set<Building>
}

class Building {
    +id: String
    +name: String
    +energyClass: String (A/B/C/D)
    +address: String
    +constructionYear: Integer
    +owner: User
    +images: Set<Image>
    +profilePhoto: Image
    +additionalEntries: Set<AdditionalEntry>
}

class Image {
    +fileName: String
}

class AdditionalEntry {
    +name: String
    +content: Object
    +isPublic: Boolean
    +unit: String
}

class User {
    +username: String
    +email: String
    +password: String
    +buildings: Set<Building>
    +comments: Set<Comment>
}

class Comment {
    +text: String
    +user: User
    +building: Building
    +timestamp: DateTime
}

class Administrator extends User {
    +idCardNumber: String
}

' Relationships
WebPortal --> "1..*" Building : has
Building --> User : owner
Building --> "0..*" AdditionalEntry : has
Building --> "0..*" Image : has
User --> "0..*" Comment : creates
User --> "0..*" Building : creates
User --> "0..*" AdditionalEntry : manages
Administrator --> User : manages
Administrator --> Comment : deletes

' Use Cases
usecase "Register" as UC_Register for Visitor
usecase "Confirm Email" as UC_ConfirmEmail for Visitor
usecase "Create Building" as UC_CreateBuilding for User
usecase "Manage Entries" as UC_ManageEntries for User
usecase "Comment on Building" as UC_CommentBuilding for User
usecase "Search Buildings" as UC_SearchBuildings for Visitor
usecase "Activate Account" as UC_ActivateAccount for Admin
usecase "Setup User" as UC_SetupUser for Admin
usecase "Delete Comment" as UC_DeleteComment for Admin
usecase "Release Entry Publicly" as UC_ReleaseEntry for User

' Associations between use cases and actors
Visitor --> UC_Register
Visitor --> UC_ConfirmEmail
Visitor --> UC_SearchBuildings
User --> UC_CreateBuilding
User --> UC_ManageEntries
User --> UC_CommentBuilding
User --> UC_ReleaseEntry
Admin --> UC_ActivateAccount
Admin --> UC_SetupUser
Admin --> UC_DeleteComment

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements

- **Actors**: `Visitor`, `User`, and `Administrator` are the main actors interacting with the system.
- **Classes**:
  - `WebPortal`: Represents the web portal with its version and URL, and maintains a catalog of buildings.
  - `Building`: Contains details like name, energy class, address, etc., and is linked to an owner user.
  - `Image`: Stores image file names, including the profile photo.
  - `AdditionalEntry`: Holds textual or numeric data with optional public visibility.
  - `User`: Regular users who can create buildings, manage entries, and comment.
  - `Comment`: A comment made by a user on a building.
  - `Administrator`: Special type of user with additional administrative functions.
- **Relationships**:
  - One-to-many relationships between `WebPortal` and `Building`.
  - One-to-many relationships between `User` and `Building`, `Comment`, and `AdditionalEntry`.
  - `Administrator` inherits from `User`.

---

### ✅ 10 Meaningful Use Cases

| Use Case Name               | Actor     | Description                                                                 |
|----------------------------|-----------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Register                   | Visitor   | Visitor registers with a username, email, and password.                    |
| Confirm Email              | Visitor   | Visitor confirms their email via a link sent after registration.          |
| Create Building            | User      | User creates a new building in the system.                                 |
| Manage Entries             | User      | User adds, edits, or deletes additional entries for a building.           |
| Comment on Building        | User      | User comments on another user's building.                                  |
| Search Buildings           | Visitor   | Visitor searches for buildings using full-text search.                     |
| Activate Account           | Administrator | Administrator activates a user account after setup.                      |
| Setup User                 | Administrator | Administrator sets up a new user account.                                |
| Delete Comment             | Administrator | Administrator deletes a comment from a building.                          |
| Release Entry Publicly     | User      | User makes an additional entry publicly accessible.                        |

---

### 🧠 Notes

- The diagram uses **generalization** (`Administrator extends User`) to show that administrators are a special type of user.
- Relationships like `has`, `creates`, and `manages` are modeled to reflect business logic.
- The `AdditionalEntry` class supports both text and numeric values, with optional unit and public visibility.

